    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund graves for babies regardless of gestational age",
        "additional_details": "However, if a baby dies after 24 weeks of gestation the costs of burial or cremation are covered through the Children\u2019s Funeral Fund for England. We ask that the Government extend this already existing Fund to provide for parents who wish to bury their child of under 24 weeks gestation, or have an individual cremation.",
        "background": "If a baby dies before the 24th week of pregnancy and the parents choose to have a burial they are charged fees by local councils for the baby's grave. These fees vary widely from \u00a3150 to \u00a31,000 plus. ",
